This chunk of code sits within a larger document discussing the implementation details of the `DirectContext` class in Panda3D, which handles mouse and keyboard input for 3D manipulation. The specific chunk deals with initializing additional tracking devices (Radamec or Fastrak) if specified during configuration, allowing for more advanced user interaction capabilities beyond basic mouse and keyboard controls.

if radamec:
                from direct.directdevices import DirectRadamec
                self.radamec = DirectRadamec.DirectRadamec(radamec)
            if fastrak:
                from direct.directdevices import DirectFastrak
                # parse string into format device:N where N is the sensor name
                fastrak = fastrak.split()
                for i in range(len(fastrak))[1:]:
                    self.fastrak.append(DirectFastrak.DirectFastrak(fastrak[0] + ':' + fastrak[i]))
